Sentencas: In this work, bi-layered Fe-Ni-Co-YSZ/YSZ nanostructured composites for solid oxide fuel cells were obtained using the spark plasma sintering (SPS) technique.
Titulo: Metal-Ceramic/Ceramic Nanostructured Layered Composites for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Spark Plasma Sintering

Sentencas: The microstructures of the anode and electrolyte were controlled by optimization of SPS consolidation parameters.
Titulo: Metal-Ceramic/Ceramic Nanostructured Layered Composites for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Spark Plasma Sintering

Sentencas: The resulting bi-layers have a full dense YSZ electrolyte and porous Fe-Ni-Co/YSZ anode as well as crack-free and well-bonded anode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Metal-Ceramic/Ceramic Nanostructured Layered Composites for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Spark Plasma Sintering

Sentencas: On the other hand, SPS under non-optimized processing parameters cannot yield the desired results.
Titulo: Metal-Ceramic/Ceramic Nanostructured Layered Composites for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Spark Plasma Sintering

Sentencas: The high resistance to thermal stresses of the fabricated half-cells was achieved with Fe-Ni-Co/YSZ anode.
Titulo: Metal-Ceramic/Ceramic Nanostructured Layered Composites for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Spark Plasma Sintering

Sentencas: The developed anode showed higher thermal compatibility with YSZ electrolyte than usual Ni/YSZ cermet.
Titulo: Metal-Ceramic/Ceramic Nanostructured Layered Composites for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Spark Plasma Sintering

Sentencas: Thus, with the successful combination of SPS parameters and anode material, we have obtained bi-layers for SOFCs with required microstructure and thermal compatibility.
Titulo: Metal-Ceramic/Ceramic Nanostructured Layered Composites for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Spark Plasma Sintering
